The paper proposes a framework for fleet management using reinforcement learning, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves coordination among a large number of agents, which suggests the possibility of multi-agent systems (MAS) and multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL), leading to cs.MA as the third likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep reinforcement learning (DRL) and the need for efficient fleet management, which could lead to cs.RO and cs.SY as the fourth and fifth likely sub-categories, respectively.
